                             In the name of Allah

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is the standard (ISIRI 2901:1994 [1]) Persian keyboard layout driver for
MS Windows.

It is created using MS Keyboard Layout Creator 1.4 [3]. But MSKLC.exe needs to
be patched to allow ZWNJ for Shift+Space. Don't worry, because I've already
done the hard part for you! You'll only need to apply MSKLC.exe.bsdiff to
MSKLC.exe using bsdiff [2] binary diff/patch tool.

The layout itself is defined in Persian.klc which can be loaded an compiled in
the patched MS Keyboard Layout Creator 1.4.

You can easily create an SFX installer using 7-zip [4]. If you're using the
command line interface of 7-zip, SFX config file would be similar to
standard-persian-keyboard.7z-sfx.conf.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[1] http://www.isiri.org/std/2901.htm
[2] http://www.daemonology.net/bsdiff/
[3] http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=82315&clcid=0x409
[4] http://7-zip.org/

